<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-05-02T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-02T16:00:00-05:00" n="1150" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1150">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/4–2747: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-05-02T17:00:00-04:00">May 2, 1947—5
                                p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>523. Informative report on Executive Office Embtel 909 Apr 27 appreciated. In
                        light Presidential Directive authorizing establishment <pb facs="1447" n="1437" xml:id="pg_1437"/> Office which stated ExOff to assist
                        Ambassador exercise overall supervision coordination basic US policies with
                        respect to military activities, it is assumed ExOff review 159 ship program
                        mentioned final paragraph your reftel is for purpose of advising Ambassador
                        concerning possible military aspects such program.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>